communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: CRC Meeeting Audio 10-2023
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

Audio recording(s) and notes from the October 11, 2023 Community Relations Commission Meeting.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Niles Coalition

communications.subject: Texas Public Information Act Request: Texas HHS Emails
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

A spreadsheet, text file, or other machine readable document(s) containing all emails sent or received from a hhs.texas.gov email address from January 1, 2020 to January 1, 2021. In particular, I am requesting the data contain the following columns: 
- email address of the sender
- email address of the receiver (including ccs)
- Date and time email was sent
- Full legal name of the sender
- Full legal name of the receiver (if they are a TX HHS employee)

If the dataset that crosswalks email addresses and names is a different file, I am happy to link it with the main dataset myself. 

Please note that I am not requesting any information about the subject or body of the emails.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ben Goehring

title: Police 9-1-1 records for 305 W Park Dr Raleigh, NC 27605

communications.subject: North Carolina Public Records Law Request: Police 9-1-1 records for 305 W Park Dr Raleigh, NC 27605
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the North Carolina Public Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

A copy of the list of 9-1-1 and/or non-emergency incident call logs between January 1, 2020, and the date of fulfillment, for 305 W Park Dr Raleigh, NC 27605.

All incident reports from and relating to 305 W Park Dr Raleigh, NC 27605 between January 1, 2020, and the date of fulfillment.

I request that you release records for this request on a rolling basis as they become available and in electronic form.

If your agency does not maintain these public records, please let me know who does and include the proper custodian's name and address.

If you choose to deny this request, please provide a written explanation for the denial including a reference to the specific statutory exemption(s) upon which you rely. Also, please provide all segregable portions of otherwise exempt material.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Albert Serna Jr.
